POLISH NEW CAR SALES UP 30 . 5 IN JAN - JUNE . New car sales in Poland grew by30 . 45 percent in January - June against the same period last yearto 262 , 219 units , an independent car market monitoring agency , Samar , said in a report . Samar said sales of commercial vehicles rose 16 . 8 percentto 25 , 933 over the same period . Fiat topped the list ofpassenger makers with 90 , 522 units sold and a 34 . 5 percentmarket share . PASSENGER CARS SALES ( UNITS ) MARKET SHARE ( PCT ) Jan - June 97 Jan - June 96 Jan - June 97 Jan - June 961 . Fiat 90 , 522 84 , 275 34 . 5 41 . 92 . Daewoo 65 , 679 42 , 325 25 . 1 21 . 13 . GM - Opel 22 , 848 14 , 563 8 . 7 7 . 24 . Renault 13 , 872 14 , 418 5 . 3 7 . 25 . Skoda 11 , 453 7 , 180 4 . 4 3 . 66 . Ford 10 , 126 5 , 940 3 . 9 3 . 07 . SEAT 8 , 106 5 , 410 3 . 1 2 . 78 . Volkswagen 7 , 770 5 , 803 3 . 0 2 . 99 . Peugeot 6 , 178 4 , 367 2 . 4 2 . 210 . Citroen 5 , 960 3 , 123 2 . 3 1 . 6 COMMERCIAL VEHICLES SALES ( UNITS ) MARKET SHARE ( PCT ) Jan - June 97 Jan - June 96 Jan - June 97 Jan - June 961 . Daewoo - Lublin 6 , 493 5 , 376 25 . 0 24 . 22 . Daewoo 6 , 415 8 , 159 24 . 7 36 . 73 . Fiat 2 , 719 3 , 269 10 . 5 14 . 74 . Citroen 2 , 447 1 , 204 9 . 4 5 . 45 . Ford 1 , 534 873 5 . 9 3 . 9 - - Warsaw Newsroom + 48 22 653 9700 
